'''Gosling's bunting'''<ref name = "IOC"/> ('''''Emberiza goslingi'''''), also known as the '''grey-throated bunting''',<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" /> is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Emberizidae]].<ref name = "IOC"/> It is found in Africa from Mauritania and Senegal to south-western Sudan and north-eastern Democratic Republic of Congo. Its natural [[habitat]]s are dry [[savannah]], subtropical or tropical dry [[shrubland]], and subtropical or tropical dry lowland [[grassland]].<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" />

It was previously considered conspecific with the [[cinnamon-breasted bunting]].<ref name = "IOC"/>

